---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../../components/Footer.astro';
import ParallaxBanner from '../../components/ParallaxBanner.astro';
import ContactForm from '../../components/ContactForm.astro';
import { articleSchema, breadcrumbSchema } from '../../lib/schema';

const pageTitle = 'Bulverde Neighborhoods | Cody Posey Real Estate';
const pageDescription = 'Explore Bulverde, TX neighborhoods by community and price range — acreage homesites, gated communities, and Hill Country retreats north of San Antonio.';
const pageSchema = [
  articleSchema({ title: pageTitle, description: pageDescription, url: '/bulverde/neighborhoods' }),
  breadcrumbSchema([
    { name: 'Home', url: '/' },
    { name: 'Bulverde', url: '/bulverde' },
    { name: 'Neighborhoods', url: '/bulverde/neighborhoods' },
  ]),
];
---

<Layout
  title={pageTitle}
  description={pageDescription}
  schema={pageSchema}
>
  <Navbar />
  <main style="padding-top: 80px;">

    <!-- Hero -->
    <div class="bv-hero">
      <div class="bv-hero__overlay"></div>
      <div class="bv-hero__content">
        <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
          <a href="/">Home</a> <span>/</span> <a href="/bulverde/">Bulverde</a> <span>/</span> <span>Neighborhoods</span>
        </nav>
        <h1>Bulverde <span style="color:#FF1616;">Neighborhoods</span></h1>
        <p>Find the right community for your lifestyle and budget</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Intro -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="bv-page-intro bv-page-intro--centered">Bulverde offers a range of neighborhoods — from master-planned communities with full amenities to quiet subdivisions on larger lots. All are served by Comal ISD and share the area's Hill Country character.</p>
        <p style="max-width: 800px; margin: 1.5rem auto 0; color: var(--gray); line-height: 1.8; text-align: center;">Situated along Highway 281 between San Antonio and the Texas Hill Country, Bulverde has grown from a quiet rural community into one of the most desirable residential areas in the region. The appeal is straightforward: Hill Country scenery, top-rated Comal ISD schools, larger lot sizes than you will find closer to the city, and a 25 to 35 minute commute to north San Antonio or New Braunfels. Bulverde neighborhoods tend to feature more mature tree coverage and rolling terrain than flat suburban developments, giving them a distinctive look and feel. Whether you are drawn to a full-amenity master-planned community or a quieter enclave on acreage, Bulverde delivers a Hill Country lifestyle that is hard to match at this distance from major employment centers.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Neighborhoods -->
    <section class="section" style="background: var(--light-gray);">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-title">
          <h2>Bulverde <span class="accent">Communities</span></h2>
        </div>

        <div class="bv-area">
          <img src="/images/generated/neighborhoods/bv-indian-springs.png" alt="Estates at Indian Springs homes" class="bv-hood__img" loading="lazy" />
          <h3>Estates at Indian Springs</h3>
          <div class="bv-area__meta">
            <span class="bv-area__price">$400K - $700K</span>
            <span class="bv-area__district">Comal ISD</span>
          </div>
          <p>A tranquil, family-oriented gated community nestled in the Hill Country, Estates at Indian Springs offers a quiet atmosphere with beautiful views and deep 80-foot wide lots lined with mature oak trees. Residents enjoy an amenity center, pool, playgrounds, and green belts with walking trails. This is a great fit for buyers looking for space, privacy, and a true Hill Country setting. Homes in Indian Springs feature Hill Country architectural styles with stone and stucco exteriors, metal roof accents, and large windows designed to frame the natural surroundings. The gated entry provides an added layer of security and exclusivity. Floor plans typically range from 2,200 to 4,000+ square feet, with many homes featuring outdoor kitchens and extended patios that take full advantage of the scenic lot views.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bv-area">
          <img src="/images/generated/neighborhoods/bv-bulverde-village.png" alt="Bulverde Village homes" class="bv-hood__img" loading="lazy" />
          <h3>Bulverde Village</h3>
          <div class="bv-area__meta">
            <span class="bv-area__price">$350K - $550K</span>
            <span class="bv-area__district">Comal ISD</span>
          </div>
          <p>Bulverde Village offers a serene suburban lifestyle with genuine Hill Country charm, featuring mature oak-lined streets and rolling terrain throughout the community. Amenities include a community park with walking and jogging paths, basketball and sand volleyball courts, playgrounds, a splash pad, a luxurious clubhouse, and a pool. The peaceful, friendly atmosphere makes it a popular choice for families looking for convenience near schools and local services. Homes in Bulverde Village range from approximately 1,800 to 3,500 square feet with three to five bedrooms, offering options for both growing families and empty nesters looking to downsize without leaving the Hill Country. The community is located close to Highway 281, providing straightforward access to San Antonio and New Braunfels for commuters.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bv-area">
          <img src="/images/generated/neighborhoods/bv-hidden-trails.png" alt="Hidden Trails homes" class="bv-hood__img" loading="lazy" />
          <h3>Hidden Trails</h3>
          <div class="bv-area__meta">
            <span class="bv-area__price">$200K - $400K</span>
            <span class="bv-area__district">Comal ISD</span>
          </div>
          <p>Hidden Trails is a master-planned community offering a relaxed, family-oriented lifestyle with resort-level amenities including multiple swimming pools (infinity-edge, beach-entry, and Junior Olympic), a 24/7 fitness center, clubhouse, playgrounds, basketball courts, and a catch-and-release fishing pond. An extensive trail network provides options for walking, hiking, and biking. It is a solid option for first-time buyers and families looking for value in the Bulverde area without sacrificing amenities or the Hill Country lifestyle. Hidden Trails is one of the most affordable communities in Bulverde with homes starting in the low $200Ks, making it an attractive alternative for buyers who have been priced out of comparable neighborhoods closer to San Antonio. The community continues to expand with new phases and builder options, including both single-story and two-story floor plans with modern open-concept designs.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bv-area">
          <img src="/images/generated/neighborhoods/bv-johnson-ranch.png" alt="Johnson Ranch homes" class="bv-hood__img" loading="lazy" />
          <h3>Johnson Ranch</h3>
          <div class="bv-area__meta">
            <span class="bv-area__price">$350K - $600K</span>
            <span class="bv-area__district">Comal ISD</span>
          </div>
          <p>A distinctive master-planned community spanning 767 acres, with one-third dedicated to natural open space, Johnson Ranch features scenic views, mature oak trees, and extensive trails throughout. Ten distinct neighborhoods offer various home sizes and lot options, from standard to estate-sized properties. This community attracts families and move-up buyers who want built-in lifestyle features and a strong sense of community. Johnson Ranch includes an amenity village with a pool, splash pad, fitness center, and event pavilion. The community's scale means there is a neighborhood within the neighborhood for virtually every buyer type — from compact starter homes to sprawling estate lots with panoramic Hill Country views. Builders in Johnson Ranch are known for energy-efficient construction and design-forward floor plans with features like oversized islands, mudrooms, and flex spaces.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="bv-area">
          <img src="/images/generated/neighborhoods/bv-singing-hills.png" alt="Singing Hills homes" class="bv-hood__img" loading="lazy" />
          <h3>Singing Hills</h3>
          <div class="bv-area__meta">
            <span class="bv-area__price">$300K - $500K</span>
            <span class="bv-area__district">Comal ISD</span>
          </div>
          <p>Also known as The Preserve at Singing Hills, this serene, family-friendly community in the Bulverde/Spring Branch area features rolling hills and lush greenery throughout. Residents enjoy convenient access to the Guadalupe River and Canyon Lake, with homes typically offering 3 to 5 bedrooms. The peaceful setting and natural scenery make Singing Hills a popular choice for buyers who prioritize a quieter pace of life. The community sits at a slightly higher elevation than surrounding areas, providing cooler breezes and elevated views of the surrounding Hill Country terrain. Homes here feature traditional and transitional Hill Country architecture with stone and hardy board exteriors, standing-seam metal roof accents, and generous front porches. Singing Hills is ideal for buyers who want a balance between community living and rural character, with the added bonus of proximity to Canyon Lake recreation and the Spring Branch area.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- School District -->
    <section class="section">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-title">
          <h2>School <span class="accent">District</span></h2>
          <p>Bulverde is served by one of the top districts in the Hill Country</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bv-schools__grid">
          <a href="https://www.comalisd.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener" class="bv-schools__card">
            <h3>Comal ISD</h3>
            <p>One of the fastest-growing districts in Texas, Comal ISD serves the entire Bulverde area. The district is known for strong academics, modern facilities, and a wide range of extracurricular programs.</p>
            <span class="bv-schools__link">Visit Comal ISD Website →</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="section" style="background: #000; color: #fff; text-align: center;">
      <div class="container">
        <h2>Need Help <span class="accent">Narrowing It Down</span>?</h2>
        <p style="color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7); max-width: 600px; margin: 1rem auto 2rem;">I can walk you through the differences between Bulverde communities and help you focus your search on neighborhoods that match your priorities.</p>
        <a href="#contact" class="btn btn-outline">Get Help Narrowing Down Areas</a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
  <ParallaxBanner image="/images/generated/comal-river.png" />

  <section class="faq-section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions About Bulverde Neighborhoods</h2>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>What is the most affordable neighborhood in Bulverde?</summary>
          <p>Hidden Trails offers the most affordable entry point into Bulverde with homes starting in the low $200Ks. Despite the lower price point, Hidden Trails does not skimp on amenities — residents have access to multiple swimming pools, a 24/7 fitness center, playgrounds, basketball courts, and an extensive trail system. It is a particularly strong option for first-time buyers and young families who want to be in the Comal ISD school district without stretching their budget.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>Which Bulverde neighborhoods are gated?</summary>
          <p>Estates at Indian Springs is the primary gated community in Bulverde, offering a controlled-access entry that provides added privacy and security. Homes in Indian Springs sit on deep 80-foot wide lots with mature oaks, and the community features an amenity center, pool, and walking trails. If you value a gated setting but also want access to master-planned amenities, Johnson Ranch includes some sections with restricted access and architectural controls that create a similar sense of exclusivity within a larger community.</p>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary>How long is the commute from Bulverde to San Antonio?</summary>
          <p>Most Bulverde neighborhoods are located along or near Highway 281, which provides a direct route south into San Antonio. The commute to north San Antonio, including the Stone Oak and TPC Parkway area, typically takes 25 to 35 minutes in normal traffic conditions. Reaching downtown San Antonio or the Medical Center takes approximately 40 to 50 minutes. The commute to New Braunfels is even shorter at about 15 to 25 minutes depending on which part of Bulverde you are leaving from.</p>
        </details>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <script type="application/ld+json">
  {
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the most affordable neighborhood in Bulverde?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Hidden Trails offers the most affordable entry point into Bulverde with homes starting in the low $200Ks. Despite the lower price point, Hidden Trails does not skimp on amenities — residents have access to multiple swimming pools, a 24/7 fitness center, playgrounds, basketball courts, and an extensive trail system."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Which Bulverde neighborhoods are gated?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Estates at Indian Springs is the primary gated community in Bulverde, offering a controlled-access entry that provides added privacy and security. Homes in Indian Springs sit on deep 80-foot wide lots with mature oaks, and the community features an amenity center, pool, and walking trails."
        }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "How long is the commute from Bulverde to San Antonio?",
        "acceptedAnswer": {
          "@type": "Answer",
          "text": "Most Bulverde neighborhoods are located along or near Highway 281, which provides a direct route south into San Antonio. The commute to north San Antonio typically takes 25 to 35 minutes in normal traffic conditions. Reaching downtown San Antonio takes approximately 40 to 50 minutes. The commute to New Braunfels is about 15 to 25 minutes."
        }
      }
    ]
  }
  </script>

  <ContactForm context="I need help narrowing down Bulverde neighborhoods..." />
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .bv-hero {
    position: relative;
    height: 280px;
    background: url('/images/generated/home-nb-modern.png') center/cover no-repeat;
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    text-align: center;
    color: #fff;
  }

  .bv-hero__overlay {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    background: rgba(0,0,0,0.55);
  }

  .bv-hero__content {
    position: relative;
    z-index: 1;
    padding: 0 1.5rem;
  }

  .bv-hero__content h1 {
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem);
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
  }

  .bv-hero__content p {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.7);
    font-size: 0.95rem;
  }

  .breadcrumb {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
  }

  .breadcrumb a {
    color: rgba(255,255,255,0.5);
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .breadcrumb a:hover {
    color: #FF1616;
  }

  .breadcrumb span {
    margin: 0 0.3rem;
  }

  .bv-page-intro {
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    color: var(--gray);
    line-height: 1.8;
    max-width: 800px;
  }

  .bv-page-intro--centered {
    text-align: center;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--black);
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  /* Area Cards */
  .bv-area {
    background: #fff;
    border-radius: 8px;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .bv-hood__img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 200px;
    object-fit: cover;
  }

  .bv-area h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
    padding: 1.5rem 2rem 0 2rem;
  }

  .bv-area__meta {
    display: flex;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
    padding-left: 2rem;
    padding-right: 2rem;
  }

  .bv-area__price {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #FF1616;
  }

  .bv-area__district {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    color: var(--gray);
    background: var(--light-gray);
    padding: 0.15rem 0.6rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .bv-area p {
    color: var(--gray);
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    padding-left: 2rem;
    padding-right: 2rem;
  }

  .bv-area p:last-child {
    margin-bottom: 0;
    padding-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  /* Schools */
  .bv-schools__grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
    gap: 1.5rem;
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .bv-schools__card {
    display: block;
    background: #fff;
    padding: 2rem;
    border-radius: 8px;
    box-shadow: 0 2px 12px rgba(0,0,0,0.06);
    transition: transform 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .bv-schools__card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-4px);
    box-shadow: 0 8px 24px rgba(0,0,0,0.1);
  }

  .bv-schools__card h3 {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 1rem;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.04em;
    margin-bottom: 0.75rem;
    color: #000;
  }

  .bv-schools__card:hover h3 {
    color: #FF1616;
  }

  .bv-schools__card p {
    color: var(--gray);
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .bv-schools__link {
    font-family: var(--font-heading);
    font-size: 0.78rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.06em;
    color: #FF1616;
  }

  /* FAQ */
  .faq-section { padding: 4rem 0; background: #f9f9f9; }
  .faq-section h2 { text-align: center; margin-bottom: 2rem; }
  .faq-list { max-width: 800px; margin: 0 auto; }
  .faq-item { background: #fff; border: 1px solid #eee; margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .faq-item summary { padding: 1.25rem 1.5rem; font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; font-size: 1rem; list-style: none; display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; }
  .faq-item summary::after { content: '+'; font-size: 1.3rem; color: #FF1616; font-weight: 700; }
  .faq-item[open] summary::after { content: '\2212'; }
  .faq-item p { padding: 0 1.5rem 1.25rem; color: #555; line-height: 1.8; font-size: 0.95rem; }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .bv-area__meta {
      flex-direction: column;
      gap: 0.5rem;
    }
  }
</style>
